text.section:
Before a license expires, the licensee may renew the license for an additional 2-year term if the licensee:
Is otherwise entitled to be licensed;
Pays to the Board:
The required renewal fee set by the Board; and
Any outstanding fees; and
Submits to the Board:
Satisfactory evidence of compliance with the continuing education requirements established under subsection (e) of this section;
Satisfactory evidence of compliance with the insurance requirements established under § 17-302 of this subtitle;
Satisfactory evidence of the resolution of any license violations, suspensions, denials, revocations, or other Board actions taken under this title; and
A renewal application on the form that the Board provides.
